{\sum_{i = 1}^n{\left(\frac{S-s_i}{S}\right)^S}}
s_i
S
 \sum_{i=1}^{\infty} s_i = S 
 \sum_{i=1}^{\infty}\left(\frac{S - s_i}{S}\right)^S 
 \lim_{i\to \infty} s_i = 0. 
 \lim_{i\to \infty}\left(\frac{S - s_i}{S}\right)^S \neq 0. 
\begin{align} \sum_{i=1}^n \frac{S - s_i}{S} &= \frac{1}{S}\sum_{i=1}^n S - s_i \\&= \frac{1}{S}\left[nS - \sum_{i=1}^n s_i\right] \\ &= n - \frac{1}{S}\sum_{i=1}^n s_i. \end{align} 
 \sum_{i=1}^n\frac{S-s_i}{S}=\sum_{i=1}^n\left(1-\frac{s_i}{S}\right)=n-\frac{\sum_{i=1}^ns_i}{S}=n-\frac SS=n-1
